expose the data only down a single level for leadership/managers? Meaning
they can see their team, but not the individuals within the teams of their
team unless their direct report is inclined to share/engage? More or less so
the most senior part of the organization cannot drill down to specific
individuals at the lowest point in the org without having a conversation
with the supervisors and leadership team along the way.  Happy to discuss in
more detail on our next call. 

Cheers,

David 

 

 

